(44, 19, 18, 45, 10, 10, 10, 'confessed, and shewed their deeds', 'Connection of Confession and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of confession in the process of faith. Acts 19:18 highlights the act of confessing deeds, while Romans 10:10 states that confession is integral to salvation.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 19, 32, 5, 5, 'confessed', 'Confession of Sin', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession. Acts 19:18 mentions believers confessing their deeds, while Psalms 32:5 speaks of acknowledging and confessing transgressions to the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 40, 3, 6, 6, 'confessed', 'Confession and Baptism Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession related to faith and repentance. In Acts, believers confess their deeds, while in Matthew, individuals confess their sins before baptism.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 3, 16, 21, 21, 'confessed, and shewed their deeds', 'Confession of Sins Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession regarding sins. In Acts, believers confess their deeds, while in Leviticus, Aaron confesses the iniquities of Israel over the goat. This connection highlights the communal aspect of acknowledging wrongdoing.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 3, 26, 40, 40, 'confessed, and shewed their deeds', 'Confession of Iniquity', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession regarding wrongdoing. Acts 19:18 highlights believers confessing their deeds, while Leviticus 26:40 speaks of confessing iniquity. This connection highlights the importance of acknowledging one''s sins.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 18, 33, 27, 28, 'confessed, and shewed their deeds', 'Confession and Deliverance', 'Both passages emphasize the act of confession as a means of deliverance. In Acts, believers confess their deeds, while in Job, acknowledging sin leads to salvation from the pit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 18, 20, 28, 13, 13, 'confessed', 'Confession and Forgiveness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of confession for receiving mercy. Acts 19:18 highlights believers confessing their deeds, while Proverbs 28:13 states that confessing and forsaking sins leads to mercy.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 19, 44, 13, 8, 8, 'curious arts', 'Connection of Sorcery and Faith', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between faith and sorcery. In Acts 19:19, the burning of books related to ''curious arts'' signifies a rejection of such practices, while Acts 13:8 shows Elymas the sorcerer opposing the faith.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
