(44, 19, 19, 5, 7, 25, 26, 'burned them before all men', 'Burning of Abominable Items', 'This connection highlights the act of burning items associated with idolatry and the rejection of abominations. Both passages emphasize the importance of destroying objects that are considered cursed or an abomination to God.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 19, 23, 2, 20, 21, NULL, 'Idolatry and Repentance', 'This connection highlights the act of discarding idols, as seen in both passages. In Acts, the burning of books represents a rejection of false practices, paralleling Isaiah''s call to cast away idols of silver and gold.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 19, 23, 30, 22, 22, 'curious arts', 'Rejection of Idolatry', 'This connection highlights the rejection of idolatrous practices in both passages. Acts 19:19 describes the burning of books associated with ''curious arts,'' paralleling Isaiah 30:22''s call to cast away graven images.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 19, 27, 2, 2, 2, 'curious arts', 'Connection of Magical Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of practitioners of magical arts. In Acts, those involved in ''curious arts'' renounce their practices, while in Daniel, the king summons ''magicians'' and ''sorcerers'' for counsel.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 20, 44, 6, 7, 7, 'the word of God', 'Growth of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the growth and increase of the word of God, highlighting its powerful impact on the community. Acts 19:20 notes that the word of God ''mightily grew,'' while Acts 6:7 states that the word of God ''increased,'' showing a consistent theme of expansion.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 19, 20, 44, 12, 24, 24, NULL, 'Growth of the Word of God', 'Both passages emphasize the growth of the word of God, highlighting its powerful impact in the early church. The phrases ''grew'' and ''multiplied'' suggest a theme of increasing influence and acceptance.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
